			<div class="content" id="post-content-3829260">
									

<p>This is the kind of &quot;political&quot; quarrel I was trying to avoid. I don't think this argument needs to at all address the agreeableness or disagreeableness of the specific sentiment concerned or to what degree the users of the site agree or disagree with the sentiment. Not only is it irrelevant, but it has the potential to stir strong emotional reaction and conflict that could be entirely avoided.</p>
<p>This is a question of atmospheric, aesthetic, narrative, and immersive disruption. The sentiment behind the alleged disruption is only pertinent insofar as the question of whether or not said sentiment (and/or the alleged disruption itself) is disruptive to the overarching atmosphere, aesthetics, narrative, and/or immersive qualities of the site as a whole.</p>
<p>Let's leave some pots unstirred, or at least stirred outside of this particular discussion. I'm not pointing fingers, just giving some words of caution to all the readers of and contributors to this discussion.</p>

							</div>

								
					
