			<div class="content" id="post-content-3829296">
									

<p>Oh, I know, but thank you for pointing it out anyway. I actually like the non-rainbow banner; the flat color scheme and plain text that I've grown to be familiar with adds to the experience in a small but non-zero way.</p>
<p>But for the average Joe, and <strong>especially newcomers</strong>, they are only exposed to the default layout. Since this is the case, I think it would be best to preserve the atmosphere in the default layout; the fact that the atmosphere is already &quot;semi-broken&quot; doesn't really make me feel motivated to break it further, nor does it discourage me from attempting to repair it.</p>
<p>Also, I can certainly appreciate the positive effects on users, potential users, and the larger site-wide community, but I think those effects can be achieved by other means, and as such should not necessarily overrule legitimate concerns with the negative effects, at least on their own. Basically, we could have our cake and eat it too if we served it in a different way.</p>

