														</div>
			</div>
			<div class="content" id="post-content-3829305">
									

<p>It's difficult to oversell the positivity that placing a pride symbol on the top of your website produces. You can expend several hundred thousand words to assure LGBTQ communities that this is a place open to their lives and their experiences &#8212; but you'll never inspire a <em>fraction</em> of the faith that a rainbow colored SCP logo produces.</p>
<p>I understand where you're coming from, and I don't think you're anti-LGBTQ; I also think you probably don't understand how reassuring it can be to see something like that for someone who's used to occupying spaces where their identity is under perpetual attack. It's like being lost at sea during war, spotting an approaching ship &#8212; and then seeing that they're flying <em>your</em> flag.</p>
<p>It means a tremendous amount &#8212; and while I understand and respect the damage it does to your immersion, that immersion is no where near as important to me as signaling to others that this community is a positive, open, and welcoming place.</p>

							</div>

								
					
